---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'June 5, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy policy for Digital Factory — how we collect, use, and protect your information."
  canonical="https://yourdomain.com/privacy"
  type="website"
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16">
    <header class="mb-10">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-primary dark:text-white mb-3">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-500">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-dark max-w-none">

      <p>
        This Privacy Policy describes how Digital Factory ("we", "us", or "our") collects, uses,
        and shares information when you visit <strong>https://yourdomain.com</strong> (the "Site").
        By using the Site, you agree to the practices described in this policy.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

      <h3>Information you provide</h3>
      <p>
        We do not require you to create an account or submit personal information to read content
        on this Site. If you contact us by email, we collect the email address and any information
        you include in your message.
      </p>

      <h3>Information collected automatically</h3>
      <p>
        When you visit the Site, standard web server logs may record your IP address, browser type,
        referring URL, pages visited, and the date and time of your visit. This data is used solely
        for operating and improving the Site and is not sold or shared with third parties for
        marketing purposes.
      </p>

      <h3>Cookies and local storage</h3>
      <p>
        The Site uses browser <code>localStorage</code> to remember your display preference
        (light or dark mode). No tracking cookies are set by this Site. Third-party services
        embedded on the Site (see Section 3) may set their own cookies subject to their own
        privacy policies.
      </p>

      <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Deliver and maintain the Site</li>
        <li>Understand how visitors use the Site in aggregate, to improve content and performance</li>
        <li>Respond to emails or enquiries you send us</li>
        <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information to any third party.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Third-Party Services</h2>

      <h3>Gumroad</h3>
      <p>
        Some articles link to products sold through Gumroad (<a href="https://gumroad.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">gumroad.com</a>).
        When you click a Gumroad link and make a purchase, you are subject to Gumroad's own
        <a href="https://gumroad.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Privacy Policy</a>
        and <a href="https://gumroad.com/terms" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Terms of Service</a>.
        We do not receive or store your payment information.
      </p>

      <h3>Cloudflare</h3>
      <p>
        This Site is hosted on Cloudflare Pages. Cloudflare may process request data (such as IP
        addresses) as part of its infrastructure and security services. Please review
        <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Cloudflare's Privacy Policy</a>
        for details.
      </p>

      <h3>RSS Feed</h3>
      <p>
        We offer an RSS feed at <a href="/rss.xml">/rss.xml</a>. RSS reader applications may
        collect usage data according to their own privacy policies. We do not collect information
        about RSS subscribers.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Data Retention</h2>
      <p>
        Server log data, if retained, is kept for no longer than 90 days and used only for
        security and operational purposes. Email correspondence is retained only as long as
        necessary to resolve your enquiry.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        This Site is not directed to children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect
        personal information from children. If you believe a child has provided us with personal
        information, please contact us and we will delete it promptly.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on your location, you may have the right to access, correct, or request deletion
        of any personal data we hold about you. To exercise these rights, contact us at the email
        address below. We will respond within 30 days.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Links to Other Sites</h2>
      <p>
        The Site contains links to external websites. We are not responsible for the privacy
        practices or content of those sites. We encourage you to review the privacy policy of any
        site you visit.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will revise the
        "Last updated" date at the top of this page. Continued use of the Site after changes
        are posted constitutes your acceptance of the updated policy.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:<br />
        <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:privacy@yourdomain.com">privacy@yourdomain.com</a>
      </p>

    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
